<br>
I believe Warcraft 3 is a single player and multiplayer game.  And I think the Multi-play part is free. <br>
<br>
I know how you feel about another monthly payment.  It seems you have to pick one and stick with it.  Unfortunately this means that not as many people will be playing other games as EQ strives to remain the king.  <br>
<br>
There have been other Online subscription games I have wanted to check out including Asheron's Call, Dark Age of Camelot, Anarchy Online and the upcoming Shadowbane.  But they all seemed to be offshoots of EQ... even Anarchy Online with its future setting... Plus they had a dismal launch.  I love jumping into other worlds... Unfortunately my wallet and my free time are making it rather difficult to check out everything I have an interest in.<br>
<br>
And Wynd, <br>
<br>
Speaking of SWG (Star Wars Galaxies) I have been looking forward to that one as well.  I have heard rumors that since it's by Sony Online Entertainment... They may do a deal if you have both EQ and SWG.<br>
<br>
Have you ever played Jedi Knight II?  It was a first person game where you got to play a Jedi and wield a lightsaber.  That was damn cool!<br>
<br>
I think my perfect game would be where you could explore and role play on a bunch of alien worlds...(like EQ or SWH) But have it more action oriented like Jedi Knight or Half-Life... Then jump in your ship and travel to other planets... with plenty of space combat dogfighting as in Freespace 2 or the Star Wars X-Wing series...   Oh and have thousands of folks playing simultaneously online!<br>
<br>
Now that game would kick ass!<br>
<br>
I wonder how many CDs and hard drive space that would use up?<br>
